==Physiological roles==

P2X receptors are involved in a variety of physiological processes,<ref name="North"/><ref name="pmid16885977">{{cite journal | author = Khakh BS, North RA | title = P2X receptors as cell-surface ATP sensors in health and disease | journal = Nature | volume = 442 | issue = 7102 | pages = 527–32 | year = 2006 | pmid = 16885977 | doi = 10.1038/nature04886 | issn = }}</ref> including:
* Modulation of cardiac rhythm and {{tsl|en|contractility||contractility}}<ref name="pmid11274344">{{cite journal | author = Vassort G | title = Adenosine 5'-triphosphate: a P2-purinergic agonist in the myocardium | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_physiological-reviews_2001-04_81_2/page/767 | journal = Physiol. Rev. | volume = 81 | issue = 2 | pages = 767–806 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11274344 | doi = | issn = }}</ref>
* Modulation of {{tsl|en|vascular resistance||vascular tone}}<ref name="North"/>
* Mediation of [[疼痛|nociception]], especially {{tsl|en|chronic pain||chronic pain}} <ref name="pmid11734618">{{cite journal | author = Chizh BA, Illes P | title = P2X receptors and nociception | journal = Pharmacol. Rev. | volume = 53 | issue = 4 | pages = 553–68 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11734618 | doi = | issn = | url = http://pharmrev.aspetjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/53/4/553 }}</ref>
* Contraction of the [[输精管|vas deferens]] during [[射精|ejaculation]]<ref name="North"/>
* [[血小板|Platelet]] aggregation<ref>{{cite pmid | 16402906}}</ref>
* [[巨噬细胞|Macrophage]] activation<ref>{{cite pmid | 19214778}}</ref>
* [[细胞凋亡|Apoptosis]]<ref>{{cite pmid | 22349510}}</ref>
* [[神經元|Neuron]]al-[[神經膠質細胞|glial]] integration<ref>{{cite pmid | 22879061}}</ref>

==Tissue distribution==

P2X receptors are expressed in cells from a wide variety of animal [[组织_(生物学)|tissues]]. On presynaptic and postsynaptic {{tsl|en|chemical synapse||nerve terminals}} and [[神經膠質細胞|glial]] cells throughout the [[中樞神經系統|central]], [[周围神经系统|peripheral]] and [[自主神经系统|autonomic]] nervous systems, P2X receptors have been shown to modulate {{tsl|en|chemical synapse||synaptic transmission}}.<ref name="North"/><ref name="pmid10823099">{{cite journal | author = Burnstock G | title = P2X receptors in sensory neurones | journal = Br J Anaesth | volume = 84 | issue = 4 | pages = 476–88 | year = 2000 | pmid = 10823099 | doi = | issn = | url = http://bja.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/84/4/476 }}</ref> Furthermore, P2X receptors are able to initiate [[肌肉收缩|contraction]] in cells of the [[心肌|heart muscle]], [[骨骼肌|skeletal muscle]], and various [[平滑肌|smooth muscle]] tissues, including that of the [[循环系统|vasculature]], [[输精管|vas deferens]] and [[膀胱|urinary bladder]]. P2X receptors are also expressed on [[白血球|leukocytes]], including lymphocytes and macrophages, and are present on blood [[血小板|platelet]]s. There is some degree of subtype specificity as to which P2X receptor subtypes are expressed on specific cell types, with P2X<sub>1</sub> receptors being particularly prominent in smooth muscle cells, and P2X<sub>2</sub> being widespread throughout the autonomic nervous system. However, such trends are very general and there is considerable overlap in subunit distribution, with most cell types expressing more than one subunits. For example, P2X<sub>2</sub> and P2X<sub>3</sub> subunits are commonly found co-expressed in [[感覺神經元|sensory neuron]]s, where they often co-assemble into functional P2X<sub>2/3</sub> receptors.

==Basic structure and nomenclature==

To date, seven separate genes coding for P2X subunits have been identified, and named to as '''P2X<sub>1</sub>''' through '''P2X<sub>7</sub>'''.<ref name="North"/><ref name="Gever">{{cite journal | author = Gever JR, Cockayne DA, Dillon MP, Burnstock G, Ford AP | title = Pharmacology of P2X channels | journal = Pflugers Arch. | volume = 452 | issue = 5 | pages = 513–37 | year = 2006 | pmid = 16649055 | doi = 10.1007/s00424-006-0070-9 | issn = }}</ref>

